# Prototype the decision loop on replayed traffic

## Step

Cheapest touchable artifact: a throwaway Fable loop fed a real day of joelclaw message traffic (replayed from the stream/journal, not live), producing what it *would have sent* — rewrites in one voice, storm aggregations, hold/deliver choices with one-line reasons.

This is an alignment instrument, not a cutover gate. Joel ruled out a shadow window; full replacement stands. The prototype exists so Joel can react to the agent's actual judgment and voice before the decision-loop design closes — a reaction beats a discussion. Build it with the `prototype` skill: throwaway, no production wiring.

Joel touches the output (a rendered before/after of a real day) and grills: is the voice right, are the aggregations right, what did it wrongly hold or wrongly deliver.

Resolved when Joel has reacted to at least one full replayed day and the reactions are recorded as design inputs in the result section. Feeds [Design the decision loop](./design-decision-loop.svx) and [Plan the full cutover](./plan-full-cutover.svx).
